messages.text:
Thanks, Anthony, but Jeff said this in the Haven group: ".. the testnet will run for a few months and then mainnet, you'll also be one of the first to gain access so yes, you're super early"

I know that the testnet has been running internally but I get the impression from this that Jeff is talking about the public testnet (which those of us who register get early access to), then followed by mainnet for everyone (and I doubt you'd want to skip the phase of a public testnet entirely!)

So my take from what Jeff says is that mainnet live by 1/1/2024 looks unrealistic by this reckoning

Since the emission schedule for esH1 is pre-defined you could technically assign esH1 tokens to YLD holders without a mainnet in place, but they'd obviously have to wait for a functioning block chain to use them in earnest

Feel free to correct me if my understanding is off beam

You can't have the same asset being in two places at once.

text:
Hey there, Haven1 is a purpose-built Layer 1 blockchain incubated by Yield App and designed with security and scalability in mind. It combines traditional finance's recourse mechanisms and security guardrails with the unique features of the DeFi world, unlocking previously unattainable use cases. 

Haven1 utilizes an environmentally friendly Proof of Authority (PoA) consensus mechanism to enable network-level risk controls and ensure regulatory compliance without sacrificing privacy. 

You'll be able to read more here:
Please also feel free to make any question you might have, we're happy to provide you with more information.

text:
to expand on your question, Haven1 will provide a safer network for users to interact, To date, there are more than 170 active blockchains in the market, yet not a single one offers:

    Network-level risk controls

    Proper recourse mechanisms in the event of fraud or the loss of funds

    Protection against legal uncertainty

These recourse mechanisms are paramount to encourage mainstream adoption and attract billions in institutional capital that would lend legitimacy to the entire crypto market. 

The key reason for this is the irreversible nature of blockchain transactions. This leaves users at risk of losing their funds due to mistakes or fraud. At the same time, the permissionless nature of blockchain means institutions have been largely unable to participate in the burgeoning DeFi ecosystem.

Haven1 is designed to change this. At launch in 2024, Haven1 will be the first blockchain that combines the best of both worlds: security and recourse in the event of malicious activity with the exciting innovations of DeFi. 

When you have a chance, please take a moment to read one of our latest blog articles for more information:

text:
Hi Jimmy, thank you for asking, this topic has been touched multiple times in the articles when we mention future use cases for the network.

What are Haven1‚Äôs key use cases?
Haven1's provable identity framework enables a number of exciting use cases, including: 

    Reputation-based on-chain lending underpinned by real-world credit scores, in a similar fashion to traditional loan risk management best practices. This allows undercollateralized forms of lending on a mass scale, such as traditional mortgage lending. 
    The integration of real-world assets for proof of ownership. For example, non-fungible tokens (NFTs) could be utilized as proof of property ownership.
    More efficient global exchange and settlement of tokenized digital representations of traditional assets, such as bonds and commodities. This has the potential to migrate the trillions of dollars currently exchanged through traditional financial markets on-chain.

These are just to name a few, on our latest blog article we mention challenges currently found on real world assets and how we aim to address and solve them with Haven1

Hi! To participate in the testnet please follow these steps:

1) Click this link:¬†

2) Select "Join Testnet" and "Register"
3) Connect your Metamask or Wallet Connect
4) Fill in your details!
5) Refer your friends for higher priority!

What's next?

Once you're whitelisted, you'll receive an email with instructions on how to participate in the testnet. You'll also get a guide and a way to provide feedback.

üö® Remember!

Daily participation is crucial. The more active you are, the more rewards you'll receive. The most active users will get even bigger rewards. If you haven't already, join the Haven1 Telegram channel to stay updated!¬†

I meant that there are many variables that affect what the next wave looks like, I'm sure you understand that it depends on how the existing testers go.  The first wave was only 5 people who found a simple issue with the Discord verification. Had we let 1,000 people in on day one it would have been 1,000 people waiting for Discord to be fixed haha.  Second wave was about 50 people and third wave, I don't have the numbers but it was in the hundreds. Does that mean the next wave will be in the thousands? It all just depends on what transpires in the meantime.  

I think it's just important to understand that this is a real testing phase. I have no doubt at all that everyone who is currently registered will have the opportunity to participate, it's still super early.

So we went around in a circle. It seems you guys changed the rules of unstaking halfway through the promo. But the argument is "we did not change the lock-up, therefore we did nothing wrong. We only changed the unstaking rules".
You could have also made it 1 year redemption period, but then more people would be upset.

I personally dislike these kind of tactics. You implied during that promo that all tokens are unlocked and freely redeeamable instantly on Dec 31st.

Anyway, not a big issue for me aside from transparency issues, but if this is how it plays out, then I will be extremely cautious of your next lock-up promotions / promises.

messages.text:
Thank you for this new version, but I can see some areas for improvement that I shared on the chan FR :
I find that the earn function requires too many clicks and searches, especially for new users.

I also understand that yieldapp wants to promote its new 'yield pro' tool, but this is at the expense of clarity.

In reality I would have liked to see the following layout:
- No 'yield pro' line on the home page (except temporarily if there's a need to promote the product)
- An 'earn' button at the bottom of the app to replace the '+ button' (which is redundant with the home page)
- The earn page has two tabs at the top of the page: 'yield' (for classic 360, 30 and flexible yield) and 'yield pro'.

What do you think ?

To my understanding 20% means 60million H1 dedicated for YLD stakers every year for 5 years. There is no APY, only total amount of people and their coins on the platform divided by 60 million H1 each year.

-H1pool 60million
-Staked time - 1 Year
*1000 people in total stake YLD for H1
*999 of those people have 1000 YLD staked
*1 whale has 1 000 000 YLD staked
